    </section>

    <!-- Student Achievements Section -->
    <section id="achievements" class="container mb-5">
        <h2 class="section-title">Student Achievements</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">We celebrate the remarkable accomplishments of our deaf and hard of hearing students who inspire us with their dedication, talent, and perseverance. These success stories showcase the incredible potential when barriers to communication are removed.</p>
        
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="achievement-card text-center">
                    <img src="/assets/imgs/achievements/malik.jpg" alt="Malik Johnson" onerror="this.classList.add('error')">
                    <h4>Malik Johnson</h4>
                    <div class="badge-achievement">National Science Fair Winner</div>
                    <div>
                        <span class="achievement-category academic">Academic</span>
                        <span class="achievement-category leadership">Leadership</span>
                    </div>
                    <p>Malik, who was born deaf, won first place at the National Science Fair with his innovative project on visual earthquake warning systems for the deaf community. He's now pursuing engineering at MIT.</p>
                    <small class="text-muted"><i class="far fa-calendar-alt me-1"></i>May 2024</small>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="achievement-card text-center">
                    <img src="/assets/imgs/achievements/sophia.jpg" alt="Sophia Chen" onerror="this.classList.add('error')">
                    <h4>Sophia Chen</h4>
                    <div class="badge-achievement">Youth Poet Laureate</div>
                    <div>
                        <span class="achievement-category art">Arts</span>
                        <span class="achievement-category advocacy">Advocacy</span>
                    </div>
                    <p>Sophia, who is hard of hearing, became her city's Youth Poet Laureate. Her powerful sign language poetry performances have been viewed millions of times online, bringing deaf culture into the mainstream.</p>
                    <small class="text-muted"><i class="far fa-calendar-alt me-1"></i>March 2024</small>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="achievement-card text-center">
                    <img src="/assets/imgs/achievements/carlos.jpg" alt="Carlos Rodriguez" onerror="this.classList.add('error')">
                    <h4>Carlos Rodriguez</h4>
                    <div class="badge-achievement">Tech Startup Founder</div>
                    <div>
                        <span class="achievement-category professional">Professional</span>
                        <span class="achievement-category leadership">Leadership</span>
                    </div>
                    <p>Carlos, who became deaf at age 5, founded a successful tech startup that develops accessibility apps. His company recently received $2M in funding to expand their innovative tools for the deaf community.</p>
                    <small class="text-muted"><i class="far fa-calendar-alt me-1"></i>January 2024</small>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="achievement-card text-center">
                    <img src="/assets/imgs/achievements/aisha.jpg" alt="Aisha Patel" onerror="this.classList.add('error')">
                    <h4>Aisha Patel</h4>
                    <div class="badge-achievement">Paralympic Swimming Medalist</div>
                    <div>
                        <span class="achievement-category leadership">Leadership</span>
                    </div>
                    <p>Aisha, who is deaf since birth, won three gold medals in swimming at the Deaflympics. She's now mentoring young deaf athletes and advocating for more inclusive sports programs in schools.</p>
                    <small class="text-muted"><i class="far fa-calendar-alt me-1"></i>December 2023</small>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="achievement-card text-center">
                    <img src="/assets/imgs/achievements/jackson.jpg" alt="Jackson Williams" onerror="this.classList.add('error')">
                    <h4>Jackson Williams</h4>
                    <div class="badge-achievement">Robotics Competition Champion</div>
                    <div>
                        <span class="achievement-category academic">Academic</span>
                    </div>
                    <p>Jackson, who is hard of hearing, led his team to victory in the National Robotics Competition. Their robot featured innovative visual cues specifically designed with deaf users in mind.</p>
                    <small class="text-muted"><i class="far fa-calendar-alt me-1"></i>November 2023</small>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="achievement-card text-center">
                    <img src="/assets/imgs/achievements/elena.jpg" alt="Elena Vasquez" onerror="this.classList.add('error')">
                    <h4>Elena Vasquez</h4>
                    <div class="badge-achievement">Sign Language Teacher of the Year</div>
                    <div>
                        <span class="achievement-category professional">Professional</span>
                        <span class="achievement-category advocacy">Advocacy</span>
                    </div>
                    <p>Elena, who was born deaf, was recognized as Sign Language Teacher of the Year. Her innovative curriculum has been adopted by schools nationwide, helping thousands of students learn ASL.</p>
                    <small class="text-muted"><i class="far fa-calendar-alt me-1"></i>October 2023</small>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="text-center mt-4">
            <a href="#" class="btn btn-secondary">View More Achievements</a>
